HEADWORD: Bontebok
<hw>Bon"te*bok</hw> <pr>(b⟦ocr⟧n"t⟦esl⟧*b⟦ocr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[D. <ets>bont</ets> a sort of skin or fur, prop. variegated +
<ets>bok</ets> buck.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The pied antelope of
South Africa (<spn>Alcelaphus pygarga</spn>). Its face and rump are
white. Called also <altname>nunni</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

